<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 10 at 5:04PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A moderate to band of snow will impact portions of eastern Fergus
County through 545 PM MST...
At 501 PM MST, A moderate band of snow were reported along a line
extending from 8 miles east of Belt to 15 miles south of Zortman.
Movement was southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Brief period of moderate snow and winds up to 30 mph.
SOURCE...Satellite and webcams.
IMPACT...Variable visibility down to a half mile or less and
slippery roads could result in hazardous driving conditions.
Locations impacted include...
Grass Range, Roy, Fergus and Fred Robinson Bridge.
This includes the following highways...
Highway 200 between mile markers 110 and 123.
Highway 191 between mile markers 27 and 42, and between mile markers
27 and 87.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
